			<div class="content" id="post-content-4227619">
									

<blockquote>
<p>1. On the phone, let's search Moneybags' Email<br />
2. On the computer, look at the file inside of the Dumpster<br />
3. Search the Lodestar Work Orders program.<br />
4. Finally, go to the AIC Helpdesk and see if there is some way that we could report that our keycard is missing, and see if we could make a new one for us. Perhaps the Employee Database file will help, or something in the sheaf of papers mentioned before? The Badger program would probably help to make the keycard, however.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Done.<br />
Done.<br />
Done.<br />
And done&#8230;.. with one exception, and I mentioned this before, if you want to look at any papers you have to put it in your load or figure out some other clever way rather than just looking at it. Also sorry kaktus, no alex. She has bigger things to do rather than helpdesk items.</p>
<p>So there we are! Our most interactive update to date! Lot of stuff went into this one and it was a doozy to accomplish. In a late celebration of Easter, I have also planted a hidden easter egg clue in there. Have fun finding it, I promise it's not that hard to find. And so the adventure continues.</p>

